      "side": 1,
      "message": "The registration callback is attached with MoreExecutors.directExecutor() while initializeAdjRibOutTables() holds the BGPPeer monitor (@Holding(\"this\"), line\n507). Per Guava\u0027s contract, if the commit future is already complete when addCallback() runs, the callback executes inline on the calling thread — which still holds the monitor. registerPeer → onPeerAdded then acquires the LocRibWriter lock under the BGPPeer lock, the exact BGPPeer → LocRibWriter inversion against\nonDataTreeChanged → refreshRibOut (LocRibWriter → BGPPeer) that this commit sets out to eliminate. Whether the deadlock is possible depends purely on commit-completion timing.\n\nPass an executor that always dispatches, e.g. io.netty.util.concurrent.GlobalEventExecutor.INSTANCE (already used in this bundle). Do not use the\nsession\u0027s channel event loop — onPeerAdded performs the full per-table route dump and would block I/O for all peers on that loop.",
      "revId": "8768ec75cd3119eda17fa022e11699aa6bb4fab0",
      "serverId": "7fc14799-209e-464c-9743-7a06c2c21a81"
    },
